==English==
=== Etymology ===
From U.S. [[slang]]
=== Adjective ===
'''gnarly''' 
# [[unkempt]], in [[disrepair]]
#: ''His shack was '''gnarly'''.''
# smelling bad
#: ''The crab bait was '''gnarly'''.''
# looking rugged or [[weatherbeaten]]
#: ''Keith Richards has a '''gnarly''' face.''
# [[cantankerous]]
#: That was one '''gnarly''' [[vagrant]] we arrested last night.
# really nice!
#: ''That is a '''gnarly''' skateboard, Dude.''
# [[expensive]]-appearing
#: ''Look at this '''gnarly''' gear.''
# [[modern]] or [[current]]
#: He used a '''gnarly''' piece of machinery to shine that stone.

=== Interjection ===
'''gnarly'''  
# really nice!
#: '' '''Gnarly''', Dude!''
# bad or disgusting
#: '' '''Gnarly'''!  You're going to eat that?''